  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>The Hotel Allalin is a family run hotel in Saas-Fee, it has been in the Zurbriggen family since 1928 and currently run by the fourth generation family members. The family</span><span> pride themselves on high standard accommodation and cuisine, and will be sure to provide a warm welcome. </span>Located in the picturesque resort of <a data-udi="umb://document/f1003f9fd15e4187b02398fa5c12dc50" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f1003f9fd15e4187b02398fa5c12dc50}" title="Saas Fee">Saas Fee</a>, the Hotel Allain is surrounded by towering peaks and glaciers, offering breath-taking views and convenient access to the region's ski slopes.</p>
<h2>Traditional and cosy</h2>
<p>Each of the rooms at the Hotel Allain combine traditional <span>wooden furniture and warm colours with more modern design and amenities,</span> plus many of the rooms offer incredible views of the surrounding mountain peaks. After a day of skiing on the slopes of Saas Fee relax with a drink at the Casanova bar, it is a lovely spot to catch up with family and friends. There is also a sauna and relaxation area, if you want a moment of peace. </p>
<h2>Rustic restaurant </h2>
<p>The Walliserkanne restaurant is the only remaining part of the old building, <span>hand-carved wooden furniture throughout. D</span>ine by candlelight surrounded by a 350-year-old larch wood and enjoy the delicious cusine on offer. Each day enjoy an extensive breakfast buffet which offers a classic continental offering, as well as additional hot options. Dinner consists of five courses, combining Swiss classics with innovative touches.</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
